&quot;During contract negotiations, it&#039;s important to distinguish *between* the sales representative presenting the offer and the manager who has the final *approval* power on pricing.&quot;
&quot;Before negotiating a marketing *contract* with a new agency, research their past clients, areas of *expertise*, and success rates in campaigns similar to ours.&quot;
&quot;Negotiating a new lease agreement *involves* the landlord, the tenant (my company), and potentially the building management company responsible *for* maintenance.&quot;

&quot;Before negotiating a new *contract* with a vendor, discuss their negotiation style and potential sticking points with your sales *team*.&quot;
“By *anticipating* the possibility that the client might request a longer payment term, we can prepare alternative solutions, such as a staged payment plan, to address their *concerns* while staying within our financial limits.&quot;
&quot;Instead of asking &#039;Is price your main concern?&#039;, ask &#039;What *factors* are most important to you in reaching a final agreement?&#039;&quot;
&quot;By actively *listening* to the supplier&#039;s concerns about production costs, we might *discover* they&#039;re open to discussing alternative materials that could be mutually beneficial.&quot;
